metadata:
  section_id: 20
  section_name: رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی رفتار مبارک کا بیان
  hadith_first: 119
  hadith_last: 121

hadiths[3]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
119,"""I heard my maternal aunt relate, on the authority of her paternal uncle; 'While I was walking in Medina, someone behind me said: ‘Raise your loincloth, for that is more pious and conducive to longer wear.’ Lo and behold, he was Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace)', so I said: ‘O Messenger of Allah, it is simply a black garment with white stripes!’ He said: ‘Do you not have an example in me?’ so I looked and noticed that his loincloth was to half his shins'.”",,,119,"Al-Ash'ath ibn Sulaim said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی رفتار مبارک کا بیان
120,"""'Uthman ibn 'Affan used to wear a loincloth reaching the middle parts of his shins, and he said: 'In this manner was the loincloth of my Companion', meaning the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace).”",,,120,"llyas ibn Salama al-Akwa reported that his father said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی رفتار مبارک کا بیان
121,"""Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) took hold of the calf of my legs or his leg, and he said: 'This is the position of the loincloth, and if you object, then somewhat lower down, but if you object, the loincloth has no right to the ankles'.”",,,121,"Hudhaifa ibn al-Yuman said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی رفتار مبارک کا بیان
